name: Jessica McDonald
bio: Get Un-Stuck, Remember who you are and live the life of your dreams!
caption: When you are going through something big it can feel like you’re in that place AGAIN! But the truth is you’ve overcome many things and need to take a minute to remind yourself of that. You’ve probably overcome more things than you can count but your mind is just focused on the pain of the current experience and how hard it is. Remind yourself of all the other times you came through blithe other side. Remind yourself of what it felt like to get that victory after all the hard work! Didn’t answer a toxic call? VICTORY! Set a boundary? VICTORY! Had the courage to cry? VICTORY! Had the courage to be honest with yourself? VICTORY! Sometimes we have to be our own cheerleader. You aren’t going through this alone. We are all growing together. Hang in there! You got this!! My sweatshirt is another by ODAFT! Just ten minutes from Yew Tee MRT lies the newly revamped Stagmont Park, which is home to not one, but THREE playgrounds! This includes a three-storey treehouse playground, a toddler-friendly play zone and even a mini obstacle course for little ninjas.

𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝘆𝗼𝘂’𝗹𝗹 𝗹𝗼𝘃𝗲:
- With three sizeable playgrounds, there's plenty for kids of all ages here!
- There are plenty of sheltered areas, as well as nearby toilets with water coolers
- The park is stroller-friendly and has beautiful footpaths for a walk or jog, too!
- BBQ pits and basketball courts make this park a strong contender for your next family hangout

𝗪𝗵𝗲𝗿𝗲? Choa Chu Kang Street 54

name: Wan To Play Singapore
bio: A FUN PLAYFUL HAVEN IN SG
caption:
Sticky ball pits? Dusty sand pits? Always a bath needed after playtime? At Wan To Play, you can totally relax!

▪️ Every branch is deep-cleaned monthly by a professional team—every corner and even equipment gaps are spotless.
▪️ Ball pits are next-level! Each ball gets a special machine wash and UV sterilization—kids can hug and even chew them, no worries.
▪️ Sand pits are cleaned with a sand washer—soft, clean, and refreshing to touch. Bare feet? Totally safe. No more brushing sand off at home!

Best part? It’s super fun too! Themed zones let kids play all day, and birthday parties even get 2 hours of free play. With 8 branches across Singapore, you can choose any location.

Parents, take note! Finally, you can let the kids play and enjoy some phone time in peace 😄

name: Checkin Mummies
bio: Join a group where mummies 🤰🏻🇸🇬share knowledge & free giveaway 👇😊
caption:
Hey Pregnant Mummies Do you know that you can get up to $13,000 of Cash Gift & (CDA) benefits under the Baby Bonus Scheme? Your newborn child may be eligible for the Baby Bonus if: - he or she is a Singapore Citizen - and if the parents are lawfully married You can join the Scheme on behalf of your child as early as 2 months before their estimated delivery date. Now, let’s talk about the Cash Gift first. For your 1st and 2nd child, the Cash Gift amount you can receive is $11,000. While for your 3rd and subsequent child, is $13,000. After joining the Scheme, you can expect to receive the 1st instalment of the cash gift within 7 to 10 working days of your child's birth registration. The remaining instalments are then disbursed every 6 months till your child turns six-and-a-half years old. (will show table below on reel)(voiceover)
And you can use the cash gift freely to pay for your child's expenses. Next, let’s talk about the benefits of (CDA) Child Development Account (CDA) is a special savings account that you can open for your child at any of these banks. (will list out the banks on reel) (voiceover) So What’s so special about this saving account? 1st, the Government will deposit $5,000 into this account.
2nd, you can enjoy dollar-for-dollar matching from the Government when you save into this account, up to the Govt co-matching cap of $4,000 - $15,000. You can save & use the funds until 31st Dec of the year your child turns 12 years old. Lastly the funds can be used for many purposes at many places. Visit our website on what the money can be used on.

name: ollie | career, money & life ✨
bio: ✨sharing some big sister life advice I wish I had
caption:
Growing up in a typical Chinese Singaporean family, my parents were always very cagey about their finances. Till today, I have no idea how much money my dad earns.

As a child, I remember feeling very confused about my family’s financial position because my dad constantly made comments like “this is so expensive” or “I’ll just order the cheapest thing on the menu”

As a result, I’m now all for salary transparency.

That said, ofc you should only share it with people you feel safe sharing with and not with those who would potentially harass you lol

For me, my goal is to encourage other people to negotiate for better $$$ and to encourage those who’ve been thinking about a career switch to consider tech sales if your priority is to make money

📩 DM me if you want to learn how to get started in tech sales

name: Mummy & Zayn
bio: I am a little boy, exploring the beautiful world ❤️
caption:
🇸🇬 A weekend activity to nurture artistic interest 🎨
It was my child’s first time trying pottery, and he was incredibly focused and happy throughout! From handling the soft clay to crafting his own piece, he was fully immersed in the process. Even though he got clay all over himself, he truly enjoyed it.
💰 Pricing:
Beginner trial class is $45, which includes materials for one finished product and a 30-minute guided session. If you want to glaze the piece, it’s an extra $5. The final product will be a meaningful keepsake!
👦 Recommended Age:
The trial class is suitable for kids aged 4 and above. As long as your child can sit independently and operate the pottery wheel with guidance, they can join too.
👩‍🏫 Instructor:
The teacher was extremely patient, demonstrating step-by-step how to shape the clay and even helping touch up the kids’ work to improve the final quality. The teacher’s encouragement really boosted the kids’ confidence and helped nurture their patience and artistic interest.
🎨 After glazing and firing, we’ll be able to collect the finished pottery in 2–3 months. Can’t wait to see how it turns out! #weekendgowheresg #kidsactivities #sggowherewithkids #weekendvibes #kidsweekendactivity #potteryforkids

name: zul’s food journal 😯
bio: idk why i put this off for the longest…but here i am, ready to eat 🍽️
caption:
some of yall might say “omg i can’t believe i have to do this for the next 40-50 years” and i really don’t disagree……….. 🫩🥀 but my advice: add more self-care activities that you can do regularly, whether it’s working out, cooking, gaming, creating etc. they’ll give you a sense of ownership over your time and keep you sane. and once you’re happy with a set number of regiments, figure out a schedule for all these.
it’s not easy and it takes time, but if you’re willing to commit to the slow process, you’ll eventually find value in your personal life. and then your life revolves less around work, even if you’re committed to excellence when you’re on the clock.

name: kalynarmstrong
bio:
✨Healing, Motherhood, & Soul Growth ✨
IG: @she_returns_home
caption:
It’s okay to grieve the parenting journey you thought you’d have.

It doesn’t mean you love your child any less.
It doesn’t mean you’d trade them.
It just means… you’re human.

Maybe you pictured ease.
Or playdates without meltdowns.
Or outings that didn’t end in exhaustion.
Maybe you imagined a version of motherhood that didn’t require you to be everything, all the time.

And when reality looks different—when your child has high needs, big emotions, or invisible challenges—
You might feel guilty for grieving what could’ve been.

But grief doesn’t make you ungrateful.
It makes you honest.
And honoring that grief is how we make space for acceptance—not force it.

You’re allowed to miss the dream and love the child in front of you.
Both can be true.
And both deserve your tenderness. #G#GrievingTheDreamC#ConsciousParentingS#SoulLedMotherhoodG#GentleParentingJourneyP#ParentingAsASoulPathI#ItCanBeHardAndHolyB#BothCanBeTrueH#HighNeedsParentingI#InvisibleDisabilitiesAwarenessC#CycleBreakerMamaN#NeurodivergentParentingB#BigFeelingsLittleBodiesE#EmotionalSafetyMattersH#HealingInRealTimeU#UnspokenGriefY#YouAreNotAloneMamaS#SacredParentingR#RadicalAcceptanceP#ParentingThroughGriefAnchorForMyChild

Now 7 months old and born in Kuala Lumpur 🇲🇾 — is the calmest little baby we’ve ever known.

She doesn’t demand attention.
She just quietly studies the world like a tiny philosopher.

She’ll sit back, lock eyes with you, and just watch.

Not in a blank way — in a “I’m processing everything you just did” kind of way 😂.

Every day with her is slow, sweet, and surprising 💐.

And we’re learning to see the world the way she does — one quiet, thoughtful moment at a time.

We love her more than words can say. 💛

caption:
🇺🇸 AOH Veterans Spotlight: SFC Tom Noonan, AOH Division 59, Chicago, IL 🇺🇸

Today, we honor Sergeant First Class (SFC) Tom Noonan, a proud member of AOH Division 59 in Chicago, IL. SFC Noonan served in the U.S. Army with distinction, participating in key missions during Desert Storm/Desert Shield and the 1989 Coup in the Philippines.

Throughout his service, SFC Noonan exemplified the commitment and courage of a true leader, navigating some of the most critical operations of his time. His dedication to his country and community continues to inspire those around him.

Thank you, SFC Tom Noonan, for your service and the enduring legacy you bring to the Ancient Order of Hibernians and beyond. ☘️

name: Ali Stoner
bio:
MasterChef Australia 2022 🧡
Modern food - Scottish accent 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿
caption:
🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿 MILLIONAIRE SHORTBREAD 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿
This was my ultimate fave tray bake when I was a kid, and I have been asked for this recipe so many times! I was looking through mums old recipe book from the 70s & 80s and found this old supplement on traybakes. The language used is so old fashioned, but the recipes are still true. I only tweaked this slightly, but checked with mum and it was the recipe she used when we were kids! Thankyou to whatever magazine or newspaper this originally came from, it’s damn delicious! Fills an 8” x 10” (20 x 26cm) tin
Shortbread 150g plain flour/50g corn flour (starch)- sifted 160g butter (softened)
85g caster sugar
Pinch salt
Combine all ingredients in a stand mixer with a paddle attachment and mix till combined. Roll out to a rough rectangle no bigger than your greased tin and place within. Cut to fit using excess to fill corners. Prick all over with a fork and bake at 160c (fan forced) for 20 mins. Cool in tin.
Caramel
160g butter
160g soft brown sugar
395g tin sweetened condensed milk
3 tbsp golden syrup
1 tsp smoked salt flakes
Few drops vanilla essence
Put all ingredients apart from salt and vanilla into a saucepan and heat gently till combined. Simmer and stir for at least 10-15 minutes till darker in colour & thickened. Add the salt and vanilla essence and mix well, pour carefully over the shortbread and tap tin on worktop to distribute evenly. Pop into fridge to set.
Once set, melt 80g of each plain and dark chocolate. Stir thoroughly then pour over the caramel. Tap tap tap on worktop to level out and back in fridge to set.
Using a sharp knife cut into squares and enjoy! I like keeping mine in fridge - enjoy ☺️ #shortbread #millionaire #caramel #chocolate #rovinghaggis

name: wellystranger
bio:
Motherhood yaps & baby led weaning journey + recipe!🤍
 
 💌: Frncinefyq@gmail.com
caption:
Both of you stole the gentlest moments of my motherhood — moments I should’ve been allowed to savour, not survive.
 
 The two of you did it while wearing rings that were meant to symbolize loyalty and love.
 
 You didn’t just break promises to your spouses — you shattered a mother and her child’s life.
 
 Two people, bound by vows, yet unbothered by the wreckage you left behind.
 
 You wore commitment like a costume — and called betrayal “love.”
 
 You’re always going to be a villain in someone’s story but something never change, it’s patterns. It’s all about patterns. Time will tell, time will heal. 
 
 Nevertheless, everything in life happens for me, not to me. It’s a blessing in disguise 🤍
 
 But I have the one thing you can’t touch, my son.
 
 End of a chapter, and the beginning of a whole new story. 🤍

caption: 📍 Air Force Museum, 400 Airport Road, Singapore 534234 💰 FREE for all visitors, even tourists 🕐Tue – Sat | 9am – 4pm (closed on Sundays, Mondays, Public Holidays, Christmas Eve, New Year’s Eve & Lunar New Year’s Eve) ❗️The museum will be open on 10 August, Sunday, in celebration of National Day 2025. 👶🏻 Perfect for kids aged 2-12 yo Maybe it’s because we’ve been seeing fighter jets in the sky due to NDP rehearsal, the boys have taken a liking to jets, helicopters and airplanes! This is such a great gem for the boys to explore the different aircrafts and what it means to be a pilot or aircraft member! This museum by RSAF is an amazing way to expose kids and toddlers to how their future will look like if they aspire to be a part of the team! The different commands, badges and short film was really engaging and the boys loved it! What’s even better is that it is SHELTERED! Though outdoors, it was not hot at all. And level 2 is air-conditioned! 🥳 Theatrette Timings: 10am, 11am, 12pm, 1pm, 2pm & 3pm Key notes: ✅ FREE PARKING!! And no need to walk far at all! Parking is right next to the museum!👍 ✅ Book ticket via website and ticket allows entry for the entire day ✅ super great playground alternative if your kids like airplanes, fighter jets and helicopters! #airforcemuseum #freekidsplay #sgkids #sgfreeplay #sgplay #sgkidsplay #kidsplayground #kidsplayfun #outdoorkids #kidsfun #kidshavefun #kidsoutdoorfun #shelteredkidsplay #airforcemuseumkids #airforcemuseumplay  created by doublehadventures with TATANX's Happy Trip Adventure

bio: All the best things to do, eat and see in Singapore with kids. Tag @sassymamasg when you’re out at fun places for a chance to be featured!
caption:
𝗧𝗛𝗜𝗦 𝗝𝗨𝗦𝗧 𝗜𝗡: 𝗡𝗘𝗪 𝗣𝗘𝗧𝗧𝗜𝗡𝗚 𝗭𝗢𝗢 & 𝗣𝗟𝗔𝗬𝗚𝗥𝗢𝗨𝗡𝗗𝗦 @ 𝗦𝗚 𝗭𝗢𝗢 𝗞𝗜𝗗𝗭𝗪𝗢𝗥𝗟𝗗⁠
⁠
Exciting news! Singapore Zoo’s KidzWorld has just announced revamped playgrounds, a new petting zoo and the water play area has also changed (gone are the slides and there are water fountains instead).⁠
⁠
Highlights:⁠
- The new petting zoo has 250 animal residents, including cats, chickens, rabbits, horses and even dogs that you can interact with.⁠
⁠
- There’s a new playground with a tunnel slide, bucket netted swing and sunken trampoline.⁠ Bring hats as there’s not much shade.
⁠
- The outdoor water play area has changed - there are new water fountains (called a water maze) and water buckets but the main slide structure has now gone.⁠
⁠
- Join the Ranger Buddies on an exciting learning adventure with indoor and outdoor animal interactions, new animal programmes and even a phygital experience that incorporates modern technology. ⁠
⁠
Click the link in bio for all the deets and our kid-friendly guide to Singapore Zoo! ⁠
⁠
📍 Singapore Zoo, 80 Mandai Lake Road, Singapore 729826⁠
🗓️ Open daily from 8:30am to 6pm ⁠
💰 Tickets start from $32.40 per child and $45 per adult⁠

caption:
Sharing my quick weekday dinner fix!

Using Unagi in Teriyaki Sauce from @theseafoodcompany.sg , I can whip up a dinner real quick on a busy weekday evening 😍

SEACO Unagi comes in a frozen ready to eat pack. I just airfry it for about 10 mins, fry an omelette , some sliced cucumbers and put them altogether in a bowl and dinner is served! 

My kids love Unagi! 

Unagi, the Japanese eel contains a great assortment of vitamins and minerals, including vitamins A, D, E, B1, B2, B12 and phosphorous. 
This mineral is especially important to health because it helps to balance your body’s PH levels, improve digestion and metabolism, and enable the body to better absorb nutrients.
Unagi is also high in omega-3. It helps to improve blood pressure, lower cholesterol and reduce the risks of diabetes and arthritis. So it's really a great food for everyone in the family.

Receipe ( Serves 1 )

1 fillet of Seaco Frozen Unagi in Teriyaki Sauce
1 egg
1 Cucumber 
1 bowl of cooked rice
Furikake and Sesame seeds for toppings

1. Airfry 1 fillet of Seaco Unagi in Teriyaki sauce for about 10 mins
2. Fry an egg omelette 
3. Sliced some cucumbers
4. Place the airfried unagi, egg omelette and cucumbers on top of a bowl of cooked rice and sprinkle with some furikake and roasted sesame seeds.

Dinner is ready!

Love that homecooked dinner can be ready in no time!

caption:
I love doraemon! 
I love doraemon! 
I love doraemon! 
I need to repeat 3 times because I genuinely do!

2 more days before The Doraemon Exhibition Singapore 2022-2023 ends at @natmuseum_sg! It was an amazing experience for me and my family! My kids seriously enjoyed themselves there! 

Showcasing at the National Museum of Singapore, it is the first global showcase outside of Japan.

Showcasing Doraemon through the lens of 28 leading contemporary Japanese artists & arts groups, the artworks on display respond to the theme of “Create Your Own Original Doraemon”.

Featuring distinctive artworks that capture the artists’ memories of Doraemon & their take on Doraemon, the exhibition presents a diverse mix of ideas, mediums & techniques that include paintings, sculptures, graphics & photography. 2 artworks by Singaporean artists are also exclusively presented as part of this showcase.

The Singapore edition of the exhibition also features a selection of the Fujiko F Fujio Museum’s prized drawings & sketches by the late Doraemon creator Mr Fujiko, in a rare feature titled “MANGA DORAEMON Original Drawings Exhibition” - Act 3!

You can also look forward to exciting complementary offerings including a pop-up café and a retail experience with limited edition Doraemon collectibles.

There are a total of 3 Acts! I personally love Act 2 the most! Do note that Act 3 does not allow any photography except for the photo spot within. Tickets are sold at $30 per adult and $25 for those under 18. Kids below 6 are free! It’s open from 10am to 7pm so do pop by real soon! You will have a dorae-ffic time there!

caption:
Home!! An Ode to Singapore at 60! 🇸🇬❤️

So proud to call Singapore our home. It’s the place where our daughters grew up, nurtured in an environment that values education, respect, discipline, and kindness.

As Singapore turns 60, there are countless stories of how this nation has shaped families. Jim and I chose Singapore after traveling across 116 countries and earning a Guinness World Record. We had seen the world, and we hoped we were choosing wisely. Singapore didn’t just meet our hopes: it exceeded them!

Over the years, this small & mighty nation grew into an impressive, resourceful world-class city, and gave our family roots, community, and a deep sense of belonging. We are fortunate to have some of our dearest friends here, and grateful to wake up each day in the +65, to eternal summer, and to a country that continues to grow from strength to strength.

We’re so proud of Singapore, of her evolving story, and honored to be even a tiny blip in her incredible journey.

Happy 60th, Singapore! You gave our daughters roots to stand tall, wings to chase their dreams, and the unshakable spirit to always jia you. 💪🤩🫰

At BPA, most of our girls start young, around 4 to 6 years old, when their bodies are still super adaptable. That early start helps them develop confidence and control in extreme ranges of motion. 

Our flexibility training always follows a routine: warm-up → dynamic stretches → technique drills → active + static flexibility → cooldown.

And yes—we lift weights, we do core work, and we build serious strength to match our flexibility. Our hips, glutes, and shoulders work just as hard as our hamstrings.

Once we’ve nailed our basics (splits, bridges, backbends), some of us move into advanced work like oversplits. We use blocks, bands, and even partners to safely push beyond 180°.

One thing we never forget? RECOVERY matters.That’s how our girls stay strong, safe, and ready for whatever’s next. 

If you’re starting later, you can still train like we do. It just takes structure and consistency.

How am I suppose to be okay on the eve of my baby’s (yes, I still call her baby 🥺) first day of preschool?? 🥺  
  
I looked back hundreds of old videos on my phone and I honestly can’t believe my girl is ‘old’ enough to go to school.. on her own.. without her mama.   
  
She’s been SO excited for her first day. Tonight before bed, we chat about tomorrow and what she may encounter, she just nodded her head and said, “mummy, 可是我会很想你 (but I’m going to miss you so much)..”, then kept kissing and hugging me. Then she told me she wants to stay at home with me.. tbh, I’m having hard time letting go of my last baby at home. I underestimated how I would feel the night before her first day. I’m just feeling thankful that I’m able to accompany her for 3 hours on the first day. My sweet girl, you’ve overcome so many obstacles in your life, continue to hold on to your brave! ✨

𝐀𝐁𝐂 𝐒𝐨𝐮𝐩 𝐢𝐬 𝐚𝐬 𝐬𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐥𝐞 𝐚𝐬 𝐀𝐁𝐂! It’s one of my go-to soups when I’m busy and need something comforting, easy, and quick to prepare. Rich with vitamins A, B, and C from carrots, potatoes and tomatoes, it’s simply delicious and nutritious for the entire family!

❤️ Remember to 𝗟𝗜𝗞𝗘 & 𝗦𝗔𝗩𝗘 this recipe first so you can easily come back to it later!

𝐈𝐧𝐠𝐫𝐞𝐝𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬:
• 3-4pcs of chicken drumsticks
• 1 litre of water, more as needed
• 1 large carrot, peeled and cut into wedges
• 1 medium tomato, cut into wedges
• 1 medium onion, thickly sliced
• 1 corn, cut into chunks
• 3 medium potatoes, cut into wedges
• 1/4 tsp white pepper
• 3/4 tsp salts 

𝐈𝐧𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐮𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐬:
① Put the chicken into a pot of boiling water. Blanch the chicken for a minute.
② Remove any scum floating on the surface.
③ Wash the chicken under running water.
④ Put all ingredients into a pot of boiling water. Then, let it simmer at low heat for 2-3 hours or a minimum of 1.5 hours. 
⑤ Add salt and pepper to taste.

The last step is to transfer to a serving bowl and serve. ✨Easy Peasy!✨ We always love to pour it over rice or cooked macaroni too. Give it a try!

caption:
[SAVE THIS FOR YOUR TOKYO TRIP] 🇯🇵✨

While planning our Tokyo trip, we came across Oriental Hotel Tokyo Bay Urayasu, and it turned out to be such a great choice! 💯

✅ Why we loved it:
	•	Unbeatable convenience: Perfect for those heading to Tokyo Disney Resort, just 15-20 mins away!
	•	Complimentary perks: Free amenities, including PJs for both kids & adults 👘 + a welcome lounge with free-flow drinks & snacks 
	•	Gorgeous lobby church: We even saw a wedding so dreamy! 💒✨
	•	Bag storage available: Super handy if you arrive early or plan to go straight to Disneyland/Sea.

⚠️ Heads up:
	•	Strict check-in policy: 3PM means exactly 3PM! Even if you arrive earlier, you’ll have to queue before others return.
	•	Amenities section: Go early if you want to reserve toys & books for the kids!

🚍 Getting there:
	•	45 mins from Narita Airport ✈️ (We took Limousine bus service).
	•	1-min walk from Shin-Urayasu Station

For those planning a Disney adventure, this hotel made our trip so much easier! 

Definitely worth considering @orientalhotel_tokyobay if you’re visiting @tokyodisneyresort_official 🎢🎡

caption:
62g of protein + the gym is man’s best friend for a lean physique💪🏼 Save this chicken beehoon soup recipe! We make this about once a week, but Wes asks for this like every other day lol. This has stopped my husband from craving instant noodles for over a year now:)

Full recipe + ingredient swaps all listed on the blog | Comment “BEEHOON SOUP” if you want us to send you the full recipe!

Ingredients for Chicken Bee Hoon Soup:
• Chicken breast 
• Dried beehoon
• Your choice of veg (I used bokchoy)
• Ikan bilis stock powder
• Crab & anchovy sauce 
• Serve with fresh cut chilli padi & fried shallots

You only need about 5-10 minutes of active cooking, the rest is really just cooking the chicken breast unattended. This is a dinner recipe that doesn’t add to my stress at the end of the work day, I hope this helps you too and that you’ll have splendid meals at home❤️

Exciting news! Singapore Zoo’s KidzWorld has just announced revamped playgrounds, a new petting zoo and the water play area has also changed (gone are the slides and there are water fountains instead).⁠
⁠
Highlights:⁠
- The new petting zoo has 250 animal residents, including cats, chickens, rabbits, horses and even dogs that you can interact with.⁠
⁠
- There’s a new playground with a tunnel slide, bucket netted swing and sunken trampoline.⁠ Bring hats as there’s not much shade.
⁠
- The outdoor water play area has changed - there are new water fountains (called a water maze) and water buckets but the main slide structure has now gone.⁠
⁠
- Join the Ranger Buddies on an exciting learning adventure with indoor and outdoor animal interactions, new animal programmes and even a phygital experience that incorporates modern technology. ⁠
⁠
Click the link in bio for all the deets and our kid-friendly guide to Singapore Zoo! ⁠
⁠

caption:
Sharing my quick weekday dinner fix!

Using Unagi in Teriyaki Sauce from @theseafoodcompany.sg , I can whip up a dinner real quick on a busy weekday evening 😍

SEACO Unagi comes in a frozen ready to eat pack. I just airfry it for about 10 mins, fry an omelette , some sliced cucumbers and put them altogether in a bowl and dinner is served! 

My kids love Unagi! 

Unagi, the Japanese eel contains a great assortment of vitamins and minerals, including vitamins A, D, E, B1, B2, B12 and phosphorous. 
This mineral is especially important to health because it helps to balance your body’s PH levels, improve digestion and metabolism, and enable the body to better absorb nutrients.
Unagi is also high in omega-3. It helps to improve blood pressure, lower cholesterol and reduce the risks of diabetes and arthritis. So it's really a great food for everyone in the family.

Receipe ( Serves 1 )

1 fillet of Seaco Frozen Unagi in Teriyaki Sauce
1 egg
1 Cucumber 
1 bowl of cooked rice
Furikake and Sesame seeds for toppings

1. Airfry 1 fillet of Seaco Unagi in Teriyaki sauce for about 10 mins
2. Fry an egg omelette 
3. Sliced some cucumbers
4. Place the airfried unagi, egg omelette and cucumbers on top of a bowl of cooked rice and sprinkle with some furikake and roasted sesame seeds.

Dinner is ready!

Love that homecooked dinner can be ready in no time!

caption:
I love doraemon! 
I love doraemon! 
I love doraemon! 
I need to repeat 3 times because I genuinely do!

2 more days before The Doraemon Exhibition Singapore 2022-2023 ends at @natmuseum_sg! It was an amazing experience for me and my family! My kids seriously enjoyed themselves there! 

Showcasing at the National Museum of Singapore, it is the first global showcase outside of Japan.

Showcasing Doraemon through the lens of 28 leading contemporary Japanese artists & arts groups, the artworks on display respond to the theme of “Create Your Own Original Doraemon”.

Featuring distinctive artworks that capture the artists’ memories of Doraemon & their take on Doraemon, the exhibition presents a diverse mix of ideas, mediums & techniques that include paintings, sculptures, graphics & photography. 2 artworks by Singaporean artists are also exclusively presented as part of this showcase.

The Singapore edition of the exhibition also features a selection of the Fujiko F Fujio Museum’s prized drawings & sketches by the late Doraemon creator Mr Fujiko, in a rare feature titled “MANGA DORAEMON Original Drawings Exhibition” - Act 3!

You can also look forward to exciting complementary offerings including a pop-up café and a retail experience with limited edition Doraemon collectibles.

There are a total of 3 Acts! I personally love Act 2 the most! Do note that Act 3 does not allow any photography except for the photo spot within. Tickets are sold at $30 per adult and $25 for those under 18. Kids below 6 are free! It’s open from 10am to 7pm so do pop by real soon! You will have a dorae-ffic time there!

caption:
Home!! An Ode to Singapore at 60! 🇸🇬❤️

So proud to call Singapore our home. It’s the place where our daughters grew up, nurtured in an environment that values education, respect, discipline, and kindness.

As Singapore turns 60, there are countless stories of how this nation has shaped families. Jim and I chose Singapore after traveling across 116 countries and earning a Guinness World Record. We had seen the world, and we hoped we were choosing wisely. Singapore didn’t just meet our hopes: it exceeded them!

Over the years, this small & mighty nation grew into an impressive, resourceful world-class city, and gave our family roots, community, and a deep sense of belonging. We are fortunate to have some of our dearest friends here, and grateful to wake up each day in the +65, to eternal summer, and to a country that continues to grow from strength to strength.

We’re so proud of Singapore, of her evolving story, and honored to be even a tiny blip in her incredible journey.

Happy 60th, Singapore! You gave our daughters roots to stand tall, wings to chase their dreams, and the unshakable spirit to always jia you. 💪🤩🫰

📍2 Bukit Merah Central, #02-03, Singapore 159835

At BPA, most of our girls start young, around 4 to 6 years old, when their bodies are still super adaptable. That early start helps them develop confidence and control in extreme ranges of motion. 

Our flexibility training always follows a routine: warm-up → dynamic stretches → technique drills → active + static flexibility → cooldown.

And yes—we lift weights, we do core work, and we build serious strength to match our flexibility. Our hips, glutes, and shoulders work just as hard as our hamstrings.

Once we’ve nailed our basics (splits, bridges, backbends), some of us move into advanced work like oversplits. We use blocks, bands, and even partners to safely push beyond 180°.

One thing we never forget? RECOVERY matters.That’s how our girls stay strong, safe, and ready for whatever’s next. 

If you’re starting later, you can still train like we do. It just takes structure and consistency.

caption:
How am I suppose to be okay on the eve of my baby’s (yes, I still call her baby 🥺) first day of preschool?? 🥺  
  
I looked back hundreds of old videos on my phone and I honestly can’t believe my girl is ‘old’ enough to go to school.. on her own.. without her mama.   
  
She’s been SO excited for her first day. Tonight before bed, we chat about tomorrow and what she may encounter, she just nodded her head and said, “mummy, 可是我会很想你 (but I’m going to miss you so much)..”, then kept kissing and hugging me. Then she told me she wants to stay at home with me.. tbh, I’m having hard time letting go of my last baby at home. I underestimated how I would feel the night before her first day. I’m just feeling thankful that I’m able to accompany her for 3 hours on the first day. My sweet girl, you’ve overcome so many obstacles in your life, continue to hold on to your brave! ✨

caption:
𝐀𝐁𝐂 𝐒𝐨𝐮𝐩 𝐢𝐬 𝐚𝐬 𝐬𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐥𝐞 𝐚𝐬 𝐀𝐁𝐂! It’s one of my go-to soups when I’m busy and need something comforting, easy, and quick to prepare. Rich with vitamins A, B, and C from carrots, potatoes and tomatoes, it’s simply delicious and nutritious for the entire family!

❤️ Remember to 𝗟𝗜𝗞𝗘 & 𝗦𝗔𝗩𝗘 this recipe first so you can easily come back to it later!

𝐈𝐧𝐠𝐫𝐞𝐝𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬:
• 3-4pcs of chicken drumsticks
• 1 litre of water, more as needed
• 1 large carrot, peeled and cut into wedges
• 1 medium tomato, cut into wedges
• 1 medium onion, thickly sliced
• 1 corn, cut into chunks
• 3 medium potatoes, cut into wedges
• 1/4 tsp white pepper
• 3/4 tsp salts 

𝐈𝐧𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐮𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐬:
① Put the chicken into a pot of boiling water. Blanch the chicken for a minute.
② Remove any scum floating on the surface.
③ Wash the chicken under running water.
④ Put all ingredients into a pot of boiling water. Then, let it simmer at low heat for 2-3 hours or a minimum of 1.5 hours. 
⑤ Add salt and pepper to taste.

The last step is to transfer to a serving bowl and serve. ✨Easy Peasy!✨ We always love to pour it over rice or cooked macaroni too. Give it a try!

[SAVE THIS FOR YOUR TOKYO TRIP] 🇯🇵✨

While planning our Tokyo trip, we came across Oriental Hotel Tokyo Bay Urayasu, and it turned out to be such a great choice! 💯

✅ Why we loved it:
	•	Unbeatable convenience: Perfect for those heading to Tokyo Disney Resort, just 15-20 mins away!
	•	Complimentary perks: Free amenities, including PJs for both kids & adults 👘 + a welcome lounge with free-flow drinks & snacks 
	•	Gorgeous lobby church: We even saw a wedding so dreamy! 💒✨
	•	Bag storage available: Super handy if you arrive early or plan to go straight to Disneyland/Sea.

⚠️ Heads up:
	•	Strict check-in policy: 3PM means exactly 3PM! Even if you arrive earlier, you’ll have to queue before others return.
	•	Amenities section: Go early if you want to reserve toys & books for the kids!

🚍 Getting there:
	•	45 mins from Narita Airport ✈️ (We took Limousine bus service).
	•	1-min walk from Shin-Urayasu Station

For those planning a Disney adventure, this hotel made our trip so much easier! 

Definitely worth considering @orientalhotel_tokyobay if you’re visiting @tokyodisneyresort_official 🎢🎡

caption:
🍎🍐 Apple + Pear Water (suitable for babies 6M+) 

This is how I trained bb G to drink water because it’s naturally sweet, babies tend to suck more. Now she knows how to sip from her cup and she actually loves water after learning with it! 💛

Apple + pear water is so good for little ones. In TCM, snow pear is known to moisten the lungs, soothe dryness and calm little coughs, while apple is cooling, gentle on digestion, and helps regulate the tummy. Red dates add natural sweetness and are believed to nourish qi (energy) and blood, making this a comforting and nourishing drink. 

You only need 4 ingredients and 25 mins:
•⁠ ⁠1 Fuji apple (skin on, cut cubes)
•⁠ ⁠1 Golden pear (skin on, cut cubes — half if big)
•⁠ ⁠1–2 red dates (peeled & deseeded, cut small)
•⁠ ⁠500ml water 

Quick, simple, baby-approved and 2-in-1! ✨ Blend the cooked apple & pear into a smooth puree so nothing goes to waste.

We’ve been using the @pigeonsingapore Pigeon StarTouch Straw Cup designed with sensory bumps to guide lip closure, a short straw to support tongue movement, and a gravity ball so bb G can sip easily at any angle 🍼✨ Spill-proof, safe, and perfect for her straw drinking journey.

💌 Comment “apple pear water” and I’ll send you the recipe straight to your inbox!

caption:
Kid's friendly -- Milky Miso macaroni soup

Super simple but flavourful dish for Gwen. I'm using scallop and salmon for this dish, but you can also make this soup with chicken and any proteins. Ohh, now then I realise miso pair so well with milk. It can be one of our comfort dish!

Ingredients:
1/2 cup macaroni 
1/2 cup carrots
500ml water (add occasionally)
20g cubed salmon
1 scallop
Gomoku Nama Age or fried toufu
Enoki mushrooms 
2 tablespoons fresh milk

UPDATES: Stir in the miso paste after adding the milk. 

I Google after got to know that miso mixture should be added at the final stage of cooking. The nutritional benefits are damaged once it's boiled because miso is a fermented food, and it contains live, active cultures of bacteria. Thanks for letting me know about it! I shall take note 🫠

- salmon @quanshuiwetmarket

We love the baby products from Mongdies @mongdies_global from @kstyle4u_. These products are so gentle on the skin, plus they are pretty effective! 

🛁𝐌𝐨𝐧𝐠𝐝𝐢𝐞𝐬 𝐁𝐚𝐭𝐡 & 𝐒𝐡𝐚𝐦𝐩𝐨𝐨 - 𝐕𝐄𝐆𝐀𝐍
A weakly acidic, top to toe Cleansing gel matches the pH of our skin. It has great moisturing effect. Can be used from newborn. 

👶𝐌𝐨𝐧𝐠𝐝𝐢𝐞𝐬 𝐀𝐭𝐨 𝐋𝐨𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 - 𝐕𝐄𝐆𝐀𝐍
Baby skin has a weaker and more sensitive skin barrier with lesser sebum than adults thus it is essential to moisturise their skin regularly to prevent moisture from evaporating. Can be used on newborn.

caption:
Talula Hill Farm Resort in Johor is a cosy little retreat, great for a one night stay or as an add-on to a longer JB trip in Malaysia ☺️. 

🚙  travel time is ~ 1.5 hours again and a relatively convenient commute with kids if you’re going in by car.

🏡 Geared to be family friendly (we had kids + grandparents) - there are two bedders, bunk beds and even loft rooms. Simple touches like offering picnic mats, board games to your room help you enjoy family time. They planned kids activities too but we didn’t join in as we were soaking in the slow slow life. There is a campfire each Saturday night too where you probably can roast marshmallows. 

👩‍🌾 it is self contained with an in house farm cafe (which was good! Try Ayam penyet & Cajun chicken). The animal feeding, pool, event hall are all close by. It’s a hilly area and the buggy service became a highlight cos we enjoyed riding it 😆.

For the fishing, the hooks are sharp and little hands would not be as adept to work on it. Careful cos smaller kids may have the hook near eye level too. We mainly threw the fish feed into the pond so it was safer.

Accommodation is more cabin style than hotel style too ☺️

Grateful to tick this off the wish list!

caption:
Let’s start practicing good eye care habits to prevent or slow down childhood myopia! We can do this, fellow mums & dads! ❤️

More than half of children developing myopia by 12 years old and the scary part here is childhood myopia tends to progress quickly and it leads to higher levels of myopia and more eye health risks! 

Thankfully, we have the Amanda the Panda book to help us with tips for myopia management which we are going to share with you too! Because sharing is caring! ❤️

1. Let’s go out and have fun outdoor activities instead of staying indoors all the time. It can help to delay onset of myopia.
2. Bring your children for eye check-ups even they don’t wear glasses. Book here: www.snec.com.sg/myopia-centre 
3. Let’s encourage your children to relax their eyes for 3 to 5 minutes after half an hour of doing homework, reading or using electronic device 
4. Wear a pair of sunglasses with UV protection to shield children’s eyes from excessive ultraviolet rays 
5. Remember to light up adequately with a table lamp to reduce eye strain 
6. Read from a distance - at least 35cm. 50-60cm away from the computer and 2 metres or further from television 
7. Maintaining good posture is important. Consider ergonomics desk! 
8. Protective eye wear is great to prevent eye injuries when playing sports 
9. For myopic children, do consult eye care professional for advice on myopia management solution to prevent it from worsening.

Thanks to Amanda, The Panda 🐼 for teaching us more tips on myopia management and now I’m letting my kids to have fun adventures playing outdoors. My youngest kid loves her fun bubble play and it’s nice to enjoy fresh air while spending precious moment with the little ones! ❤️

#SNECMyopiaCentre #AmandathePanda @snec_seri @essilorluxottica

caption:
Last weekend, we went on a mission to collect all the 3 National Day Commerative Special Collectibles. 

We earned our 1st commerative coin when we went to @westmallsg . The girl had to go through the various army stations and get all the questionnaires correct. They got to try out wearing the army vest, The girls had fun going through the various game stations.

Secondly, we earned our second commerative coin at @singaporediscoverycentre The girls had fun making their own gasing. They also viewed the various displays inside. The girls also tried their hands on the 3D military games, each taking a role as an Airforce fighter pilot, a Army tank commander and a Navy combat ship commander, all doing their part to destroy enemy intruders! We had fun learning about Singapore.

Finally we earned our 3rd commerative coin at @singaporenavymuseum . The girls get to learn more about Singapore's Maritime History and how we have progressed over the decades. The girls had fun learning about our Maritime history, Semaphore Flag Codes, history of the RSN and more! 

Just a suggestion to drive there as there is no public transport and unlikely that taxi and private hired cars will go all the way there to pick you. We saw and heard a few families "stranded" there for a while because they couldnt get transport out. 

The commerative event is until 13Aug. Here are the websites of the 3 venues that we went. Click on the link to find out more.

Wishing everyone Happy National Day! 🇸🇬

1. West Mall
🌏https://www.westmall.com.sg/
📍1 Bukit Batok Central Link Singapore 658713

2. Singapore Discovery Centre
🌍https://www.defencecollectivesg.com/sdc/

caption:
The kind of staycay you’d have when you are parents of a toddler and young infant 😂 It’s no longer about having romantic time or sleep in like nobody’s business.

@interconsin is generally a nice hotel to stay, I like that the pool is relatively always empty and easier to book 😂 You know it can be hard to arrange with 2 young kids and their unpredictable schedule!

And their location is definitely a winning point too! Imagine that panicking moment when you realised your child’s milk is not enough! caption:
Work from home days are the best because I can cook delicious meals, can anyone else relate? 💞 

What I cooked:
Breakfast: Chia Seed Coconut Flour Spinach Pancakes 🥞 
Instead of a sweet pancake, try savoury ones! A sweet and starchy breakfast leads to a glucose spike, which hurts our body’s ability to make energy efficiently and makes us tired *cue food coma*. Learn more over at @theglucosegoddess 

Lunch: Rice Paper Rolls 🌱 
Traditionally vietnamese, but I think you can put any fillings you want, really! Mine was dependent on what I had in the fridge 😅 >>> Smoked salmon, lettuce, sauerkraut, kimchi, avocado 

Dinner: Beef Stew 🍲 
Traditional chinese medicine practice believes that foods like red meat can help nourish the blood, which is vital to circulating Qi. I personally find beef tough to cook well, so I really like this easy one pot recipe!

Did you enjoy this reel? Let me know what other content you'll like to see!

From racing in wet weather, to falling and picking herself up, to chasing and closing up the gap, to finding the gap to overtake and emerging champion in the finals. As the only girl standing on the expert podium - and at the top spot no less - our only hope is that more girls come to know about and pick up this sport! 

Thank you to everyone who has been part of her journey and who will continue to be part of her journey ❤️.

caption:
Balance? What balance. 😅
We’re just out here running on caffeine and vibes... right?

But what if you didn’t have to choose between being a present parent and getting good sleep?

As moms of two, we’ve learned that when babies sleep well, everything changes — your energy, your mood, your evenings, your life.

✨ Here are 5 tips to help your baby sleep better (and you too):

1️⃣ Stick to a predictable nap & bedtime routine
Babies thrive on consistency — simple steps like bath, book, cuddle, and sleep cue their body to wind down.

2️⃣ Keep the room cool, dark & turn on white noise
A cool (23°C), pitch-dark room with white noise blocks out stimulation and helps baby settle and stay asleep longer.

3️⃣ Feed baby at the start of their awake window (EASY routine)
Feeding right after baby wakes ensures they’re alert, helping them feed more efficiently and sleep better thereafter.

4️⃣ Give baby lots of active floor / tummy time
Movement during wake windows burns energy, builds strength, and reduces the chance they’ll want to “practise” rolling or crawling in bed.

5️⃣ Teach independent sleep skills — that’s where sleep training comes in
When babies learn to fall asleep on their own, they’re more likely to link sleep cycles, sleep through the night and take good naps without needing help.

It’s never too early or too late to start. Every baby is different — but every parent deserves rest.

caption:
[SAVE REEL & BOOK WHEN IN TOKYO] 🇯🇵I seriously found this hotel on XHS (小红书） about 2-3 weeks before we went Tokyo 😅really #lastmin🤣 #familystaysg_japan

I researched and saw a lot people raving about its convenience and complimentary benefits as such the free amenities (that includes PJ for the kids & adults) plus a gorgeous Church parked right in the middle of the lobby ~ we even witness a wedding that day and it was so whimsical 🫣💕

The bag storage is super convenient for those who arrive early and can’t check in, or if you want to head straight to Disneyland/Sea. The downside is that Japanese are strict about their check in time - 3pm means 3pm, so even we came back at 230pm, they still refused to let us do any check in and have to Queue early before anyone else gets back. 

The welcome lounge benefits only applicable for one day, and it’s really free flow - enjoy on the spot or take & go. Whereas the Amenities facilities, got to go early to reserve the toys 🧸 and books 📚 

🏨Oriental Hotel Tokyo Bay Urayasu is nestled close within a 5-minute walk from Urayasu City Traffic Playground too! We didn’t check that out but good to know! 

🚍About 10mins to 15 mins away from Tokyo Disney Resort and Tokyo International airport is 45mins away. We booked a car transfer (from airport) as we are group of 6. So really depends on how you wish to plan for your stay. We definitely enjoyed our benefits and convenience at @orientalhotel_tokyobay 👍🏻 especially those who wants to visit @tokyodisneyresort_official.

name: Ester Voon
caption:
Having live-in domestic help is something we are all familiar with in Singapore but a concept many others in the rest of the world find highly privileged. And after dealing with the bull that some of my ex helpers have given me, I first toyed with the idea of going without any domestic helpers around mid 2022. I told myself that if the two helpers I had at that time didn’t last, then it would be the last of my search efforts for a helper that would fit my household’s needs. To pave the way for this possible outcome, I started to slow down my own business and started planning for my transition to being a full time SAHM.

Fast forward to end June 2023, I sent home my last helper. I was a little fearful NGL, afterall I have never lived a day without having fewer than 2 extra hired pair of helping hands at home since I got married and started a family. My mum and mil who have been also a constant source of support and help with the kids had serious concerns. They repeatedly advised me against going without helpers and to reconsider hiring just one more so I wouldn’t “drown and die”. But my heart was set. Afterall there’s nothing I enjoy doing more than the things people think I cannot. 

I struggled, I did. But I also survived. Now 3 months into my days as a SAHM to 3 girls without any hired help, I can say that this has been the best thing I have done for our family.

My kids are still well fed and well dressed, my house is still clean and aesthetic (if I may say so myself) as hell… my mind is peaceful, I love the privacy, my husband has stepped up and became the hands on daddy of our dreams, and we have so much more time spent together with our kids. 

So here’s a reminder that ✨when you think that you can do no more, give no more… there is always more in you if you dig deeper. Nothing is truly impossible✨ it hurts a little to put my own aspirations on hold and I’m beyond exhausted most days but I’d still make the same decision again in a heartbeat. It’s truly so worth it.

caption:
We had a wild wow weekend at the @mandaiwildlifereserve celebrating the official launch of KidzWorld @ Singapore Zoo!

Packed with amazing presentations and the opportunity to get up close and even pet some of the fascinating animals.

Here are the must-see attractions within KidzWorld that added to our incredible experience:

🐾 Little Paws: A place where we made new furry and feathery friends.
🐾 Animal Land: Home to adorable falabellas, goats, chickens and more.
🐾 Animal Buddies: The heart of animal presentations and volunteer opportunities.
🐾 Animal @ Play: An area of fun and learning.
🐾 Our boys embarked on an exciting Ranger Buddies Quest and had a blast cooling off at the Splash Zone.

Make sure to grab the Ranger Buddies First Explorer Map at the Singapore Zoo and explore the C.O.U.R.A.G.E zones. Completing the mission in these zones will reward you with exclusive commemorative pins as a memento of your incredible day.

We spent the entire day here, and it was an absolute blast! We highly recommend bringing your kids along for an unforgettable adventure.

Enjoy 2-Park Wildlife Wonders Bundle at 40% off admission tickets to Singapore Zoo and River Wonders at $54 for Adult and $38 for Child. Valid till 30 Dec 2023.

caption:
We had lots of fun today cooling off at Splash-N-Surf, which is located on top of Kallang Wave Mall. Here you can find:

🔷️ Kids Water Play Area - which consists of a range of water slides and water fountains.
🔷️ Kids Pool - which is a 60cm deep pool & has a set of bucket water swings.
🔷️ Lazy River - is 1m deep and has a gentle current so you can laze in a tube and float around the pool. What's great is they even have some little tubes suitable for toddlers.

📍 Splash-N-Surf, Level 3 Kallang Wave Mall Near gate 21 of National, stadium, 397629 Singapore 

⏰️ Mon, Wed, Thurs, Fri, Sat & Sun 9am to 8pm. Closed every Tues, selected public holidays (eg New Years Day, 1st day Chinese New Year, Hari Raya Puasa, Deepavali & Christmas) & it is also closed other times as published on https://www.sportshub.com.sg/announcement/splash-n-surf 
During rain, I would call before visiting to check they are still open (as I know some water play areas shut during rain).

🤑 The kids water play area & kids pool are FREE! The Lazy river is $2 per person, and you get to use a float. Note you can ride the lazy river as many times as you like and can even leave and re-enter on the same day.

👨‍👩‍👦 The kids water play area and kids pool are for kids 12 and under (with supervising adults). These areas are probably most suited for those under 6 as I think older kids may get bored (although I have received comments from others that older kids under 10 still enjoy the area). The lazy river is for everyone (again with supervising adults).

caption:
Calling first time moms struggling with in-laws questioning your parenting.

You tell yourself they mean well.
You tell yourself it’s just for a season.
But somehow, every bottle, every nap schedule, every decision—suddenly feels like it’s not yours anymore.

And the worst part? You feel guilty for feeling upset AND for not stepping in earlier.

Here are 5 ways in-laws quietly take over, leaving new moms feeling small—and what you can do about it:

1. They make themselves the “default expert.”
They say things like “This is how we did it,” or “Back in my day…” as if your instincts don’t count.

📌 Try this: “Thanks for sharing. We’ve decided to follow our paediatrician’s advice on this.”
(Gottman calls this setting a unified front. It buffers against external stress and helps to build the couple as a team.)

2. They step in before you can.
Feeding the baby, burping the baby, putting them to sleep… all before you’ve had a chance.

📌 Try this: “I appreciate the help, but I’d like to do this myself today.”
(As Nedra Glover Tawwab says: Boundaries are not just walls, they’re clarity. Telling your in law that even if it takes you longer, you'd like to handle these baby caregiving yourself provides clarity.)

3. They question your routines subtly.
“Isn’t it too early for solids?” or “She naps again?”

📌 Try this: “We’re trying what works for us. It’s okay if it looks different.”
(Brené Brown reminds us that clear is kind. Vague boundaries invite confusion.)

P.S. Even if YOU feel unsure and like you're still figuring out, it's okay to still have boundaries. 
👉 You’re just adjusting to your new identity as a mom—while trying to hold on to your voice.

Your baby doesn’t just need love.
They need a mother who feels safe and empowered to lead.

👶 Comment TALK to get the Top 12 Conversation Prompts for New Parents—designed to help you and your partner stay united when the in-laws get involved.

caption:
When my baby needs a cuddle and clings onto me like a little koala 🐨 

She's happy to be in my arms and accompanying me while I dry my hair.. to which I say to her, "Thank you for being so patient and waiting for mummy."
- - - 
Day 77 | Bathed Tia myself for the first time today, under granny's guidance 🛁

Pep talked my darling that mummy will be the one bathing her today. Asked for her patience with me, which she so kindly gave. There was no fussing as her clumsy mummy fumbled and stumbled with awkward angles and holds. Despite all that, she looked at me all starry-eyed, smiling.. aww~ *melts into a puddle*

And I said to her, "Thank you for being so patient with mummy. Mummy will get better at this. Sorry for taking too long."

It's amazing how there's someone who can make me say "thank you" and "sorry" all the time, so wholeheartedly and willingly..

I love you, Tia. So so much. 
Thank you for coming into our life.

💡Not your usual vending machine ok — this is the only vending machine in SG that serves local kopi. Freshly brewed on the spot from 100% freshly roasted beans — no corn or funny fillers added. The taste? Legit better than many kopitiams I’ve tried! And even if I leave it for a while hor, the kopi doesn’t turn sour 👏👏👏

I got my kopi from the machine at Welcia (Orchard)! 🍵 So convenient when I’m running errands or need a quick pick-me-up.

I went for my usual go-to: Kopi O with less sugar, and I was honestly impressed. Can taste the roasted notes, not too acidic, smooth and shiok to drink. And the best part — only $1 per cup 😍 Plus, they’re having a promo now: Buy 5 cups, get 1 FREE. So whenever I’m nearby, I can just redeem one easily. Really convenient for those caffeine cravings 💯

☕️ They offer 3 types of kopi with super clear labels on how much coffee/milk/sugar in each cup — great for picky drinkers like me who know exactly what they want 😅 No need to Q at kopitiam somemore — just select and collect in minutes. Faster and easier!

📍Look out for Kopi Near Me machines — especially if you’re at Orchard like me!

Here’s my quick review:
🔸Aroma: 8.5/10 – can really smell the freshness
🔸Price: 10/10 – where to find kopi at $1 nowadays?!
🔸Overall: 9/10 – solid option when I need my kopi fix fast and fuss-free!

Day started with her going for a field trip to Botanic Garden to understand about deforestation while me and the brother was scrambling to get her goodie bag prepared. Passed it to her to give it out to her classmates before bringing her to Jewel for lunch. Main purpose was to go to the Hello Kitty carnival.
